main event: A ground observer reported a sighting of a UFO over Terre Haute, Indiana on 26 March 1960.
interesting points: The UFO was observed by three diaconse e/e from a height of 22,000 feet., The observation lasted for 12-15 minutes., The UFO was described as looking like a green flare., A Delta aircraft also reported seeing the same object which leveled off and then disappeared., There were multiple conclusions drawn ranging from balloon to aircraft, indicating insufficient data for evaluation.
witness description: diaconse e/e and an unidentified pilot of Delta aircraft
